## SDQ vs RTQ

SDQ vs RTQ Comparing the Strengths and Difficulties Questionnaire (SDQ) with the Repetitive Thinking Questionnaire (RTQ) can provide valuable insights for psychologists. The SDQ focuses on the behaviour of children aged 2-17 while the RTQ explores repetitive negative thinking. These tools can provide multi-angled insights into the psychological well-being of individuals.
